A Joint Venture (JV) comprising the Nigerian National Petroleum Company (NNPC) Limited, Shell, Total and ENI, has signed a multi-million dollars deal to supply 70 million standard cubic feet (scuf) of gas to Dangote Fertiliser Company. The event, which took place at the on-going Nigeria International Energy Summit (NIES) was attended by President of Dangote Group, Alhaji Aliko Dangote; Group Managing Director of NNPC, Mallam Mele Kyari; Country Chair of Osagie Okunbor; and ENI representative.   FEC approves N3.5b for aviation equipment in Lagos, Abuja,…     Govt constitutes committee on health insurance for…     FUTO, host communities’ 10-year-old land feud worsens   Kyari said the contract was perfected within a short period based on its importance to the production of fertiliser and agro-economic growth. He said: “As you are aware, Dangote fertaliser is one of the biggest producers of fertaliser and this deal, which is to offer 70m scuf per day to Dangote fertiliser by the JV, will contribute to the surge of Fertaliser production in Nigeria. Of course, it will tremendously be posirive to our agro-economy,” Dangote stated that though the volume of gas for the deal may relatively be considered marginal, it would go a long way in promoting more access to fertiliser for the country.